Creating an API for integrating Wise.com as a payment option involves designing a backend in Python, which will handle transactions and integrate seamlessly with the Wise API. The backend will then expose endpoints that can be consumed by a Swift-based iOS app and a React frontend.

Here’s an overview of the steps:


1. Understand Wise’s API

• Visit Wise’s API documentation: Wise API Docs.

• Familiarize yourself with endpoints for:

• Creating a recipient account.

• Initiating a transfer.

• Fetching transfer status.

• Obtain an API key from Wise by signing up and creating an application.


2. Backend Implementation (Python)

Use frameworks like Flask or FastAPI to build the API.

